  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_03_ix: In the mind that is once truly disciplined and purged, thou canst not find an...",
  "body": "In the mind that is once truly disciplined and purged, thou canst not find anything, either foul or impure, or as it were festered: nothing that is either servile, or affected: no partial tie; no malicious averseness; nothing obnoxious; nothing concealed. The life of such an one, death can never surprise as imperfect; as of an actor, that should die before he had ended, or the play itself were at an end, a man might speak.",
